hands_on_practices.solution:
We wish to solve the rate equation for regenerated $\Upsilon(1S)$ mesons:
1. Volume and temperature evolution  
   $$V(\tau)=A_T\,c\,\tau,\quad 
     T(\tau)=T_0\Bigl(\frac{\tau_0}{\tau}\Bigr)^{1/3}.$$
2. Recombinant formation rate  
   $$\Gamma_{\rm form}
     =\langle\sigma_{\rm rec}v\rangle\,\frac{N_bN_{\bar b}}{V(\tau)}
     =\frac{\mathcal{C}}{T(\tau)^2}\,\frac{N_b^2}{A_T\,c\,\tau}.$$
   Since $T(\tau)^2=T_0^2(\tau_0/\tau)^{2/3}$, we have
   $$\Gamma_{\rm form}
     =\frac{\mathcal{C}\,N_b^2}{A_T\,c\,T_0^2}\;
      \frac{(\tau/\tau_0)^{2/3}}{\tau}
     =\frac{\mathcal{C}\,N_b^2}{A_T\,c\,T_0^2\,\tau_0^{2/3}}\;\tau^{-1/3}.$$
3. Integrate the rate equation  
   $$\frac{dN_\Upsilon}{d\tau}=\Gamma_{\rm form},\qquad
     N_\Upsilon(\tau_0)=0,$$
   so
   $$N_\Upsilon(\tau_c)
     =\int_{\tau_0}^{\tau_c}\!d\tau\;\frac{\mathcal{C}\,N_b^2}{A_T\,c\,T_0^2\,\tau_0^{2/3}}\;\tau^{-1/3}
     =\frac{\mathcal{C}\,N_b^2}{A_T\,c\,T_0^2\,\tau_0^{2/3}}
      \Bigl[\tfrac32\,\tau^{2/3}\Bigr]_{\tau_0}^{\tau_c}.$$
4. Express $\tau_c$ via $T_c$:  
   $$T_c=T_0\Bigl(\frac{\tau_0}{\tau_c}\Bigr)^{1/3}
     \ \Rightarrow\ \tau_c=\tau_0\Bigl(\frac{T_0}{T_c}\Bigr)^3,
     \quad\tau_c^{2/3}=\tau_0^{2/3}\Bigl(\frac{T_0}{T_c}\Bigr)^2.$$
   Hence
   $$N_\Upsilon(\tau_c)
     =\frac{\mathcal{C}\,N_b^2}{A_T\,c\,T_0^2\,\tau_0^{2/3}}
      \;\frac32\,\tau_0^{2/3}\Bigl[\Bigl(\frac{T_0}{T_c}\Bigr)^2-1\Bigr]
     =\frac{3\,\mathcal{C}\,N_b^2}{2\,A_T\,c\,T_0^2}
      \Bigl[\Bigl(\tfrac{T_0}{T_c}\Bigr)^2-1\Bigr].$$
